Hotkey?!?

Well, the only advisable hotkey is:

/stopsong
/stopsong (not really necessary to do it twice, but doesn't hurt)
/cast #

# = the spell slot the song is in.  The reason I would put two /stopsong commands in, is because it doesn't always work - or at least, it didn't.

I don't advise putting two /cast # commands in, because that's another way of stopping songs for bards.  For a caster, you can't double cast songs, so for them it's best in case they fizzle.

To twist, start a song, the second you see the message that the song took effect, stop it and start the next.  Usually this requires casting twice (once to stop the first song, and then again to start the new song).  When the second song message appears, stop it and start the next.

Once you get used to it, you'll learn the exact moment you can stop the first song and start the second BEFORE the first message appears.  But that takes time to learn.

Read through the Bard Forums, you will see better descriptions of exactly HOW to twist.

